ng with the Bitwarden Secrets Manager. This is a beta release and might be missing some functionality.","maintainers":[{"email":"mchecinski@bitwarden.com","name":"mchecinskibw"},{"email":"racosta@bitwarden.com","name":"racostabw"},{"email":"agalles@bitwarden.com","name":"agalles"},{"email":"thorrevoets@bitwarden.com","name":"fntyler"},{"email":"bbiete@bitwarden.com","name":"bbiete"},{"email":"ajmabry@bitwarden.com","name":"aj-bw"},{"email":"bsimms@bitwarden.com","name":"bribitwarden"},{"email":"apixley@bitwarden.com","name":"apixley_bw"},{"email":"vgrassia@bitwarden.com","name":"bwvgrassia"}],"readme":"## Bitwarden Secrets Manager SDK\n\nNode-API bindings for interacting with the Bitwarden Secrets Manager. This is a beta release and\nmight be missing some functionality.\n\n## Getting started\n\n```ts\nimport { BitwardenClient, ClientSettings, DeviceType, LogLevel } from \"@bitwarden/sdk-napi\";\n\n// Optional settings\nconst settings: ClientSettings = {\n  apiUrl: \"https://api.bitwarden.com\",\n  identityUrl: \"https://identity.bitwarden.com\",\n  userAgent: \"Bitwarden SDK\",\n  deviceType: DeviceType.SDK,\n};\n\nconst accessToken = \"-- REDACTED --\";\nconst stateFile = \"some/path/to/state/file\";\n\nconst client = new BitwardenClient(settings, LogLevel.Info);\n\n// Authenticating using a machine account access token\nawait client.auth().loginAccessToken(accessToken, stateFile);\n\n// List secrets\nconst secrets = await client.secrets().list();\n\n// Get a specific secret\nconst secret = await client.secrets().get(\"secret-id\");\n```\n","readmeFilename":"README.md"}